nior%20diet%20that%20is%20gentle%20on%20their%20stomach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuisana%20recommends%20choosing%20senior%20foods%20made%20with%20highly%20digestible%20protein%20sources.%20A%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fjas%2Farticle%2F88%2F4%2F1421%2F4745685%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20that%20pollock%20and%20pork%20are%20the%20easiest%20for%20dogs%20to%20digest%20and%20absorb%20nutrients%20from%2C%20although%20there's%20no%20significant%20difference%20in%20digestibility%20among%20pollock%2C%20pork%2C%20beef%2C%20and%20chicken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%20says%20some%20changes%20occur%20in%20older%20dogs'%20digestive%20tracts%2C%20such%20as%20reduced%20surface%20area%20for%20nutrient%20absorption.%20But%20generally%2C%20he%20says%20older%20dogs%20can%20digest%20foods%20and%20absorb%20their%20nutrients%20at%20nearly%20the%20same%20level%20as%20younger%20pups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20below%20picks%20for%20the%20best%20food%20for%20senior%20dogs%20with%20sensitive%20stomachs%20include%20easily%20digestible%20proteins%2C%20including%20pork%2C%20turkey%2C%20and%20chicken.%20They%20also%20include%20gut-soothing%20healthy%20extras%2C%20like%20probiotics%20and%20turmeric.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20for%20weight%20loss%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20dog%20foods%20to%20lose%20weight%2C%20including%20Wellness%20and%20Nutro%20kibble%20and%20Hill's%20wet%20canned%20food%2C%20are%20on%20a%20green%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F648368a1a460da0019243bf5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20your%20senior%20dog%20needs%20to%20lose%20weight%2C%20we%20recommend%20foods%20from%20Wellness%2C%20Nutro%2C%20and%20Hill's.%3Cp%3EWellness%3B%20Nutro%3B%20Hill's%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%20says%20obesity%20is%20an%20issue%20for%20many%20pets%20but%20is%20particularly%20problematic%20for%20seniors.%20Older%20pets%20face%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20orthopedic%20problems%2C%20such%20as%20arthritis%20and%20other%20joint%20diseases%2C%20as%20well%20as%20metabolic%20disorders%20like%20diabetes%20mellitus%20and%20hypothyroidism.%20Being%20overweight%20increases%20the%20likelihood%20of%20developing%20these%20issues%20and%20makes%20managing%20them%20more%20challenging%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20routine%20checkups%2C%20your%20veterinarian%20will%20assess%20your%20pup's%20overall%20physique%20by%20weighing%20them%20and%20scoring%20their%20body%20condition%20and%20muscle%20mass.%20You%20can%20do%20the%20same%20between%20vet%20visits%20using%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cvmcourses.com%2Fcourses%2Fmod%2Fpage%2Fview.php%3Fid%3D232%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Small%20Animal%20Veterinary%20Association%20(WSAVA)%20body%20condition%20chart%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aaha.org%2Faaha-guidelines%2Flife-stage-canine-2019%2Fnutritional-assessment%2Fbody-and-muscle-condition-score%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Animal%20Hospital%20Association%20(AAHA)%20muscle%20condition%20chart%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiving%20less%20food%20can%20be%20a%20successful%20approach%20to%20weight%20loss%2C%20but%20there%20is%20the%20risk%20of%20not%20providing%20adequate%20nutrition%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Freeman.%20Alternatively%2C%20your%20veterinarian%20might%20suggest%20a%20specialized%20weight-loss%20diet%20formulated%20to%20meet%20your%20dog's%20nutritional%20requirements%20in%20fewer%20calories.%20Our%20recommendations%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-food-weight-loss%5C%22%3Ebest%20dog%20food%20for%20weight%20loss%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20formulated%20to%20keep%20your%20pup%20fuller%20for%20longer%20without%20sacrificing%20essential%20vitamins%20and%20nutrients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Churchill%2C%20maintaining%20a%20lean%20body%20condition%20can%20extend%20your%20pup's%20lifespan%20by%20nearly%20two%20years%20and%20significantly%20reduces%20the%20risk%20and%20severity%20of%20arthritis%20and%20other%20health%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20fresh%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fresh%20foods%20from%20Ollie%2C%20Just%20Food%20for%20Dogs%2C%20and%20The%20Farmer's%20Dog%20are%20shown%20on%20a%20green%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F648368dfa460da0019243c18%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20best%20fresh%20senior%20dog%20food%20includes%20recipes%20from%20Ollie%2C%20Just%20Food%20for%20Dogs%2C%20and%20The%20Farmer's%20Dog.%3Cp%3EOllie%3B%20Chewy%3B%20The%20Farmer's%20Dog%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20pup%20always%20begs%20for%20a%20taste%20of%20your%20meals%2C%20you%20might%20consider%20preparing%20a%20freshly%20cooked%20homemade%20diet%20instead%20of%20buying%20processed%20dog%20foods.%20However%2C%20Luisana%20cautions%20that%20homemade%20diets%20are%20rarely%20complete%20and%20balanced%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20you%20formulate%20them%20with%20the%20guidance%20of%20a%20veterinary%20nutritionist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20alternative%2C%20you%20can%20try%20the%20options%20we've%20recommended%20below.%20Our%20top%20picks%20for%20fresh%20food%20for%20senior%20dogs%20are%20formulated%20to%20meet%20AAFCO%20standards%20for%20all%20life%20stages%2C%20made%20of%20easy-to-digest%20human-grade%20ingredients%2C%20and%20prepared%20with%20oversight%20from%20an%20animal%20nutrition%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20three%20recommended%20brands%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Follie-dog-food-review%5C%22%3EOllie%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fjust-food-for-dogs-review%5C%22%3EJust%20Food%20For%20Dogs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Ffarmers-dog-food-review%5C%22%3EThe%20Farmer's%20Dog%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20not%20only%20have%20high%20ratings%20but%20they%20have%20also%20undergone%20thorough%20testing%20by%20Insider%20Reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20senior%20dog%20food%3Cp%3EOur%20experts%20say%20the%20following%20criteria%20are%20important%20to%20consider%20when%20shopping%20for%20senior%20dog%20food%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAAFCO%20nutritional%20adequacy%20statement%20for%20adult%20maintenance%20or%20all%20life%20stages%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20AAFCO%20is%20a%20nonprofit%20organization%20that%20recommends%20nutritional%20profiles%20based%20on%20an%20animal's%20life%20stage.%20They%20don't%20approve%20pet%20foods%20or%20establish%20specific%20standards%20for%20senior%20dog%20foods.%20However%2C%20choosing%20a%20senior%20food%20formulated%20for%20adult%20maintenance%20or%20all%20life%20stages%20ensures%20the%20recipe%20fulfills%20the%20recommended%20protein%2C%20fat%2C%20and%20nutrient%20requirements%20of%20adult%20dogs.%20The%20best%20dog%20foods%20for%20senior%20pups%20will%20also%20contain%20beneficial%20extras%20such%20as%20glucosamine%20and%20chondroitin%20to%20support%20joint%20health%20and%20have%20fewer%20calories%20per%20serving%20than%20adult%20dog%20foods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredient%20list%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Labels%20list%20ingredients%20by%20weight%2C%20so%20the%20first%20few%20ingredients%20generally%20make%20up%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20food's%20weight.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20particular%20ingredients%20that%20senior%20dogs%20should%20avoid%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Luisana.%20However%2C%20she%20recommends%20grain-inclusive%20foods%20over%20grain-free%20foods%20due%20to%20the%20potential%20link%20between%20grain-free%20dog%20foods%2C%20especially%20those%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiauto-59028-20%26h%3Dbc326cbdae1fb87a8e9f7ebebf40ef81a96f83a6722008843d65fcc706b2bba5%26postID%3D64832d9c42282649e84bb776%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fbest-senior-dog-food%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-021-94464-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtaining%20peas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20dilated%20cardiomyopathy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuaranteed%20analysis%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Rather%20than%20fixating%20on%20dog%20food%20ingredient%20lists%2C%20our%20experts%20say%20to%20examine%20the%20guaranteed%20analysis%20of%20important%20nutrients%2C%20including%20protein%2C%20fat%2C%20fiber%2C%20and%20other%20essential%20vitamins%20and%20minerals.%20Adult%20dog%20food%20must%20have%20a%20minimum%20of%2018%25%20protein%20and%205.5%25%20fat%20to%20fulfill%20a%20dog's%20nutritional%20needs.%20As%20the%20AAFCO%20doesn't%20set%20specific%20standards%20for%20senior%20dog%20foods%2C%20the%20guaranteed%20analysis%20of%20these%20foods%20can%20vary%20significantly%20between%20recipes.%20Before%20selecting%20a%20food%2C%20our%20experts%20recommend%20asking%20your%20vet%20about%20the%20best%20food%20for%20your%20senior%20pup.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHealthy%20extras%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20best%20senior%20dog%20food%20will%20contain%20extra%20ingredients%20that%20support%20their%20unique%20needs.%20For%20example%2C%20Freeman%20and%20Welborn%20highlight%20the%20potential%20benefits%20of%20antioxidants%20in%20supporting%20healthy%20aging.%20Welborn%20suggests%20a%20diet%20rich%20in%20antioxidants%2C%20such%20as%20Purina%20Bright%20Minds%2C%20if%20your%20dog%20experiences%20cognitive%20dysfunction.%20Other%20healthy%20extras%20for%20seniors%20include%20joint-healthy%20omega-3%20fatty%20acids%2C%20glucosamine%2C%20and%20chondroitin.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECalorie%20content%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20dog's%20metabolism%20typically%20slows%20as%20they%20age%2C%20and%20many%20seniors%20are%20less%20active.%20So%2C%20senior%20dog%20foods%20usually%20contain%20fewer%20calories%20than%20adult%20formulations%2C%20according%20to%20Churchill.%20Freeman%20adds%20that%20overweight%20senior%20dogs%20are%20at%20greater%20risk%20of%20weight-related%20conditions%20like%20arthritis%20and%20diabetes.%20That%20said%2C%20feeding%20your%20dog%20less%20food%20could%20result%20in%20a%20nutritional%20deficiency.%20That's%20why%20Freeman%20recommends%20switching%20to%20a%20low-calorie%20senior%20diet%20or%20a%20weight-management%20diet%20based%20on%20guidance%20from%20your%20vet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBreed-size%20formulation%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20best%20food%20for%20your%20senior%20pup%20may%20depend%20on%20their%20size.%20Our%20experts%20say%20small%20and%20large%20breed%20seniors%20have%20different%20health%20risks%20and%20may%20also%20require%20different%20calorie%20amounts%20and%20kibble%20sizes.%20Buying%20food%20specific%20to%20your%20pup's%20size%20helps%20ensure%20they%20get%20a%20recipe%20formulated%20for%20their%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFeeding-trial%20tested%20versus%20formulated%20foods%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20best%20senior%20dog%20foods%20have%20been%20formulated%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20feeding-trial%20tested%20%E2%80%94%20to%20meet%20the%20AAFCO's%20nutritional%20standards%20for%20adult%20maintenance%20or%20all%20life%20stages.%20If%20your%20dog's%20food%20has%20an%20AAFCO%20label%2C%20you'll%20know%20the%20recipe%20fulfills%20the%20recommended%20protein%2C%20fat%2C%20and%20nutrient%20requirements%20for%20adult%20dogs.%20A%20label%20indicating%20feeding%20trials%20confirms%20the%20food's%20safety%20and%20palatability%20based%20on%20testing%20with%20a%20group%20of%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExpert%20formulations%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20dog%20food%20brands%20we%20recommend%20meet%20quality%20control%20standards.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20brand%20employs%20a%20full-time%20board-certified%20veterinary%20nutritionist%20and%20potentially%20a%20PhD-level%20animal%20nutritionist%2C%20as%20recommended%20in%20the%20WSAVA%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENext-level%20ingredients%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Next-level%20ingredients%20refer%20to%20those%20farmed%20or%20caught%20through%20humane%20and%20sustainable%20farming%20or%20harvesting%20practices.%20Although%20these%20ingredients%20may%20not%20offer%20extra%20nutrition%20to%20your%20pet%2C%20choosing%20pet%20food%20with%20ingredients%20like%20farmed%20raised%20meats%2C%20cage-free%20eggs%2C%20and%20sustainably%20caught%20fish%20helps%20you%20support%20a%20pet%20food%20company%20that%20prioritizes%20both%20animal%20welfare%20and%20sustainable%20practices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20selected%20the%20best%20senior%20dog%20food%3Cp%3ETo%20select%20foods%20for%20this%20guide%2C%20we%20spoke%20with%20two%20board-certified%20veterinary%20nutritionists%20and%20two%20small%20animal%20veterinarians.%20They%20helped%20us%20understand%20the%20unique%20dietary%20needs%20of%20senior%20dogs%20and%20what%20makes%20the%20best%20senior%20dog%20food.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20also%20had%20the%20chance%20to%20get%20input%20from%20our%20dogs%20by%20feeding%20them%20many%20different%20brands%20and%20types%20of%20food%2C%20some%20of%20which%20we%20included%20in%20this%20guide.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Nancy%20Welborn%20is%20a%20veterinarian%20and%20associate%20professor%20of%20community%20practice%20at%20Louisiana%20State%20University%20(LSU)%20School%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine.%20Welborn%20practiced%20private%20veterinary%20medicine%20for%20livestock%20and%20companion%20animals%20before%20transitioning%20to%20emergency%20small%20animal%20critical%20veterinary%20and%20then%20returning%20to%20LSU%20to%20develop%20and%20teach%20community%20practice%20at%20the%20LSU%20School%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Emily%20Luisana%20is%20a%20board-certified%20nutritionist%20and%20practicing%20clinical%20veterinary%20nutritionist%20at%20Friendship%20Hospital%20for%20Animals%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20Luisana%20is%20a%20graduate%20of%20North%20Carolina%20State%20University%20(NCSU)%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine.%20After%20several%20years%20of%20general%20practice%2C%20she%20pursued%20a%20clinical%20nutrition%20residency%20at%20NCSU%20and%20a%20fellowship%20in%20clinical%20nutrition%20at%20Blue%20Pearl%20Veterinary%20Specialty%20Hospital%20of%20the%20Carolinas.%20Her%20clinical%20areas%20of%20interest%20include%20critical%20care%20nutrition%2C%20weight%20loss%2C%20homemade%20diets%2C%20and%20disease-state%20nutrition.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Julie%20Churchill%20is%20a%20board-certified%20nutritionist%2C%20a%20Diplomate%20of%20the%20American%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Internal%20Medicine-Nutrition%2C%20and%20a%20professor%20of%20nutrition%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine.%20After%20completing%20veterinary%20training%20at%20Michigan%20State%20University%2C%20Churchill%20pursued%20Internal%20Medicine%20and%20Nutrition%20residencies%20and%20earned%20her%20Ph.D.%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota.%20Her%20interests%20include%20seeing%20patients%20in%20the%20clinic%2C%20mentoring%20students%2C%20and%20finding%20more%20effective%20ways%20to%20teach%20nutrition%20and%20facilitate%20the%20integration%20of%20nutrition%20into%20the%20care%20of%20all%20patients%20by%20healthcare%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Mark%20Freeman%20is%20a%20board-certified%20veterinarian%20and%20assistant%20professor%20of%20community%20practice%20at%20Virginia-Maryland%20College%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine.%20Freeman%20earned%20his%20BS%20in%20Biology%20at%20Morehead%20State%20University%20and%20earned%20his%20DVM%20at%20Auburn%20University.%20His%20research%20interests%20include%20animal%20behavior%20and%20molecular%20biology.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20experts%20don't%20recommend%20any%20pet%20food%20recipes%20that%20don't%20meet%20AAFCO%20nutritional%20standards.%20They%20also%20don't%20recommend%20pet%20food%20manufacturers%20that%20don't%20comply%20with%20WSAVA%20guidelines.This%20guide%20only%20includes%20complete%20and%20balanced%20foods%20that%20meet%20the%20nutritional%20needs%20of%20adults%20or%20all%20life%20stages.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESenior%20dog%20food%20FAQs%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20the%20best%20food%20to%20give%20an%20older%20dog%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20dogs%20age%20differently%20and%20senior%20dog%20food%20diets%20vary%20significantly%2C%20there's%20no%20single%20best%20senior%20dog%20food.%20Adult%20dogs%20should%20eat%20complete%20and%20balanced%20food%20formulated%20for%20adult%20maintenance%20or%20all%20life%20stages.%20The%20AAFCO%20doesn't%20set%20standards%20for%20senior%20pet%20foods%2C%20so%20senior%20dog%20food%20recipes%20can%20vary%20significantly.%20This%20makes%20it%20important%20to%20talk%20to%20your%20vet%20about%20the%20most%20appropriate%20food%20for%20your%20dog's%20specific%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EShould%20older%20dogs%20eat%20senior%20dog%20food%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20experts%20recommend%20feeding%20older%20dogs%20senior%20dog%20food%20because%20these%20recipes%20are%20tailored%20to%20their%20lifestyle%20and%20nutritional%20needs.%20Senior%20diets%20generally%20contain%20fewer%20calories%20than%20other%20adult%20dog%20foods%20due%20to%20the%20slower%20metabolic%20rates%20and%20decreased%20activity%20levels%20of%20senior%20dogs.%20Additionally%2C%20our%20experts%20suggest%20choosing%20senior%20dog%20foods%20that%20incorporate%20beneficial%20ingredients%20like%20antioxidants%2C%20glucosamine%2C%20and%20omega%20fatty%20acids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EShould%20senior%20dogs%20eat%20wet%20or%20dry%20food%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20wet%20and%20dry%20foods%20offer%20nutritious%20options%20for%20senior%20dogs.%20While%20some%20older%20pets%20who%20have%20had%20teeth%20extracted%20may%20prefer%20wet%20food%2C%20others%20prefer%20kibble%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20they%20still%20have%20their%20teeth%20or%20not.%20If%20your%20dog%20won't%20eat%20wet%20food%20but%20has%20trouble%20chewing%2C%20you%20can%20always%20soften%20their%20kibble%20with%20some%20water.%20Your%20veterinarian%20may%20recommend%20feeding%20a%20wet%20food%20diet%20if%20your%20dog%20has%20a%20medical%20condition%20or%20tends%20to%20get%20dehydrated%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EAt%20what%20age%20should%20a%20dog%20be%20put%20on%20senior%20food%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20our%20experts%2C%20dogs%20are%20considered%20seniors%20at%20different%20ages%20based%20on%20their%20breed%20size.%20Giant%20breeds%20may%20be%20considered%20seniors%20as%20early%20as%205%20years%20old%2C%20while%20toy%20breeds%20may%20reach%20their%20senior%20years%20closer%20to%20age%2010.%20It's%20not%20unhealthy%20for%20an%20older%20dog%20to%20switch%20to%20a%20senior%20diet%20based%20on%20age.%20However%2C%20Freeman%20recommends%20taking%20your%20dog's%20overall%20health%20into%20account.%20Senior%20dogs%20in%20good%20health%20may%20not%20need%20a%20senior%20diet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDoes%20senior%20dog%20food%20make%20a%20difference%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESwitching%20to%20a%20senior%20diet%20with%20more%20omega%20fatty%20acids%2C%20and%20joint-supporting%20ingredients%20can%20make%20a%20big%20difference%20in%20the%20quality%20and%20length%20of%20your%20pet's%20life.%20If%20you%20notice%20your%20older%20dog%20slowing%20down%2C%20checking%20in%20with%20your%20vet%20is%20always%20a%20good%20idea.%20They%20can%20assess%20your%20dog's%20health%20and%20recommend%20the%20best%20dog%20food%20for%20your%20senior%20pup.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-senior-dog-food%