es%20realized%20being%20leaner%20can%20make%20you%20%26quot%3Bmore%20efficient.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerbergs-meeting-with-angry-staff-after-new-layoffs-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20a%20theory%20for%20why%20tech%20layoffs%20aren't%20slowing%20down%3A%20Companies%20are%20realizing%20that%2C%20while%20painful%2C%20there%20are%20benefits%20to%20being%20%26quot%3Bleaner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DxQqsvRHjas4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Morning%20Brew%20Daily's%20podcast%20published%20Friday%2C%20the%20Meta%20CEO%20said%20companies%20are%20still%20adjusting%20to%20the%20post-pandemic%20era.%20He%20also%20discussed%20competition%20with%20Apple%2C%20among%20other%20topics%20in%20a%20wide-ranging%20interview.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20first%20wave%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20e-commerce%20sales%20went%20through%20the%20roof%2C%20which%20drove%20big%20gains%20in%20online%20advertising.%20But%20as%20people%20returned%20to%20stores%20and%20the%20economy%20adjusted%2C%20sales%20growth%20ebbed%20and%20ad%20rates%20came%20back%20to%20earth.%20Many%20companies%2C%20including%20Meta%2C%20realized%20they%20had%20overhired%20and%20had%20to%20make%20major%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20first%20wave%20of%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20the%20layoffs%20and%20stuff%20like%20that%2C%20I%20actually%20think%20that%20was%20more%20due%20to%20companies%20trying%20to%20navigate%20Covid%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said%20in%20the%20interview%20when%20asked%20if%20tech%20layoffs%20had%20to%20do%20with%20the%20AI%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20comes%20next%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20said%20that%20companies%20are%20no%20longer%20shrinking%20their%20employee%20size%20simply%20because%20of%20overhiring%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20now%20realizing%20there%20can%20be%20benefits%20to%20being%20leaner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20lot%20of%20tech%20companies%20were%20reluctant%20to%20make%20cuts%20at%20first%2C%20they%20realized%20it%20didn't%20spell%20the%20end%2C%20Zuckerberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20obviously%20really%20tough%2C%20we%20parted%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20talented%20people%20we%20cared%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said%20in%20the%20interview%2C%20speaking%20specifically%20about%20Meta's%20past%20layoffs.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20some%20ways%20actually%20becoming%20leaner%20kind%20of%20makes%20the%20company%20more%20effective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Meta%20cut%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20its%20staff%20starting%20with%20Zuckerberg's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-year-of-efficiency-working-meta-ai-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Byear%20of%20efficiency%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-office-closures-stock-price-mark-zuckerberg-earnings-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20a%20comeback%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20its%20stock%20at%20an%20all-time%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFewer%20management%20layers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20has%20been%20chopping%20management%20layers%20as%20part%20of%20this%20efficiency%20drive.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-cuts-technical-program-managers-reinterview-for-pm-roles-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20eliminating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-tpm-roles-instagram-job-cuts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etechnical%20program%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20that%20role%20is%20also%20being%20cut%20back%20across%20other%20parts%20of%20Meta.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20didn't%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20companies%20are%20still%20in%20the%20mode%20of%20thinking%20about%20efficiency%2C%20Zuckerberg%20said%20during%20the%20Morning%20Brew%20podcast.%20Many%20are%20considering%20restructuring%20the%20company%2C%20flattening%20out%20management%20levels%2C%20and%20transitioning%20to%20a%20leaner%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20like%20Microsoft%20and%20Google%20have%20continued%20to%20downsize%20despite%20solid%20earnings.%20A%20number%20of%20CEOs%20at%20companies%20like%20Amazon%20have%20mentioned%20plans%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-layoffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erestructure%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20invest%20in%20areas%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Zuckerberg%20said%20that%20he%20didn't%20think%20AI%20was%20a%20big%20part%20of%20the%20equation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20least%20for%20us%2C%20the%20AI%20stuff%20was%20not%20a%20major%20driver%20for%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CEO%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20first%20this%20overbuilding%20and%20then%20this%20sense%20of%20like%20let's%20do%20the%20best%20work%20we%20can%20by%20making%20a%20lean%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EApple%20competition%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZuck%20also%20spoke%20about%20Meta's%20intense%20rivalry%20with%20Apple.%20%3Cspan%3EZuckerberg%20and%20Apple%20CEO%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETim%20Cook%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0have%20something%20of%20a%20feud%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-facebook-inflict-pain-apple-wsj-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoing%20back%20several%20years%20now%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0And%20the%20companies%20are%20racing%20to%20become%20the%20dominant%20platform%20for%20virtual%20reality%2C%20augmented%20reali