hi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20French%20journalist%20Vanessa%20Dougnac%2C%20who%20had%20been%20the%20longest%20serving%20foreign%20correspondent%20in%20India%2C%20announced%20her%20departure%20from%20India%20on%20Friday%2C%20February%2016%2C%20after%20the%20Indian%20government%20issued%20a%20two-week%20revocation%20of%20her%20Overseas%20Citizen%20of%20India%20(OCI)%20card%20last%20month%2C%20for%20alleged%20concerns%20over%20her%20reporting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notice%20sent%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmacrons-visit-france-raises-expulsion-threat-to-french-journalist-foreign-correspondents-in-india%5C%22%3Ealso%20raised%20by%20French%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20his%20visit%20in%20January%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20Vanessa%20Dougnac%20said%20that%20she%20was%20writing%20her%20announcement%20%E2%80%9Cin%20tears%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20I%20am%20leaving%20India%2C%20the%20country%20where%20I%20came%2025%20years%20ago%20as%20a%20student%2C%20and%20where%20I%20have%20worked%20for%2023%20years%20as%20a%20journalist.%20The%20place%20where%20I%20married%2C%20raised%20my%20son%2C%20and%20which%20I%20call%20my%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20South%20Asia%20Correspondent%20for%20four%20French%20publications%2C%20Dougnac%2C%20has%20been%20informed%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20that%20her%20Overseas%20Citizen%20of%20India%20(OCI)%20card%20will%20be%20revoked%20within%20two%20weeks.%20The%20notification%20listed%20various%20grounds%20for%20the%20revocation%2C%20ranging%20from%20%E2%80%9Cmalicious%E2%80%9D%20reporting%20that%20created%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnegative%20perception%E2%80%9D%20of%20India%2C%20inciting%20disorder%2C%20not%20taking%20permission%20for%20travelling%20to%20restricted%20areas%20and%20doing%20reporting%20on%20neighbouring%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmha-issues-notice-for-cancelling-french-journalist-oci-card%5C%22%3EAfter%20the%20notice%20was%20reported%20in%20the%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20issued%20a%20statement%20refuting%20all%20accusations%20and%20asserting%20her%20full%20cooperation%20with%20the%20legal%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%2030%20foreign%20correspondents%20stationed%20in%20India%20jointly%20penned%20an%20open%20letter%20expressing%20solidarity%20with%20Dougnac%20and%20urging%20the%20Indian%20authorities%20to%20resolve%20her%20case%20promptly%2C%20ensuring%20it%20does%20not%20adversely%20affect%20her%20career%20or%20family%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20most%20recent%20statement%20released%20on%20Thursday%2C%20she%20said%20that%20was%20%E2%80%9Cbeing%20forced%20to%20leave%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%20rejection%20of%20her%20application%20to%20work%20as%20a%20journalist%20while%20living%20in%20India%20with%20OCI%20card%20in%202022%2C%20she%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CSixteen%20months%20ago%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20denied%20my%20right%20to%20work%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20providing%20no%20reasons%20nor%20justifications%2C%20and%20no%20hearing.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20Ministry%20has%20not%20once%20responded%20to%20my%20repeated%20requests%20for%20explanations%20or%20review%20of%20this%20arbitrary%20action%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20her%20notice%20from%20MHA%20last%20month%2C%20Dougnac%20said%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20accused%20her%20articles%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbeing%20%E2%80%98malicious%E2%80%99%2C%20of%20harming%20%E2%80%98the%20interests%20of%20the%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20and%20required%20me%20to%20respond%20to%20why%20my%20Overseas%20Citizen%20of%20India%20(OCI)%20card%20should%20not%20be%20cancelled%E2%80%9D.%20It%20had%20also%20claimed%20that%20Dougnac%E2%80%99s%20articles%20could%20%E2%80%9Cprovoke%20disorder%20and%20disturb%20peace%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20while%20she%20would%20continue%20to%20challenge%20the%20accusations%20legally%2C%20the%20process%20had%20taken%20a%20toll%20and%20impacted%20her%20professionally%2C%20compelling%20her%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20I%20am%20unable%20to%20work%20and%20have%20been%20unfairly%20accused%20of%20prejudicing%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20state.%20It%20has%20become%20clear%20that%20I%20cannot%20keep%20living%20in%20India%20and%20earning%20my%20livelihood.%20I%20am%20fighting%20these%20accusations%20before%20the%20competent%20forums%20and%20I%20have%20full%20faith%20in%20the%20legal%20process.%20But%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20afford%20to%20wait%20for%20its%20outcome.%20The%20proceedings%20with%20respect%20to%20my%20OCI%20status%20have%20shattered%20me%2C%20especially%20now%20that%20I%20see%20them%20as%20part%20of%20a%20wider%20effort%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20to%20curb%20dissent%20from%20the%20OCI%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20French%20journalist%20claimed%20that%20authorities%20had%20earlier%20suggested%20that%20she%20should%20stop%20reporting%2C%20but%20%E2%80%9CI%20cannot%20agree%20to%20give%20it%20up%20because%20of%20unproven%20accusations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20immensely%20grateful%20for%20the%20extraordinary%2023%20years%20I%20spent%20as%20a%20journalist%20in%20India.%20I%20led%20a%20life%20filled%20with%20adventures%20and%20interactions%20across%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20and%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20witness%20over%20two%20decades%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20history.%20Being%20a%20foreign%20correspondent%20in%20India%20seeking%20to%20share%20with%20my%20French-speaking%20readers%20the%20complexity%20and%20richness%20of%20this%20country%2C%20was%20a%20privilege%20and%20an%20honour.%20I%20will%20cherish%20the%20memories%20I%20have%20of%20the%20warmth%20of%20the%20people%20and%20the%20beauty%20of%20this%20immense%20region.%20Delhi%20was%20my%20beloved%20city%2C%20where%20I%20lived%20my%20life.%20To%20bid%20farewell%20to%20it%20now%20is%20a%20tremendous%20sorrow%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20she%20hoped%20to%20return%20to%20India%20%E2%80%9Cone%20day%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20French%20journalist%20thanked%20%E2%80%9Cindividuals%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20colleagues%20from%20the%20journalist%20fraternity%20who%20reached%20out%20to%20me%20to%20show%20their%20support%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra%20acknowledged%20that%20France%20had%20raised%20Dougnac%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20he%20claimed%20that%20the%20actions%20against%20her%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20her%20reporting.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20are%20free%20to%20do%20what%20they%20are%20accredited%20to%20do%20in%20a%20given%20space.%20But%20here%20I%20think%20the%20principal%20issue%20is%20whether%20the%20person%20is%20compliant%20with%20the%20rules%20and%20regulations%20of%20the%20state%20under%20which%20they%20come%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20at%20a%20media%20briefing%20on%20January%2026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKwatra%20claimed%20that%20France%20had%20%E2%80%9Cappreciated%E2%80%9D%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cframe%20of%20reference%E2%80%9D%20to%20look%20at%20the%20case%20purely%20through%20a%20lens%20of%20compliance%20with%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20asked%20for%20a%20comment%20from%20the%20French%20Embassy%20about%20Dougnac%E2%80%99s%20departure%2C%20but%20there%20has%20been%20no%20response%20till%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708098130000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F26182526%2FEffect-83.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Ffrench-journalist-vanessa-dougnac-leaves-india-amid-expulsion-threat%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20South%20Asia%20Correspondent%20for%20four%20Fr